                " deuterium gas target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".The STAPRE-F code was used for estimation",
                " energy-averaged cross sections for particle-induced",
                " reactions with several possible emitted particles.",
                " The neutron transmission coefficients were calculated",
                " using the ECIS03 code with the global optical model",
                " parameters by Koning and Delaroche.",
                " The energies, spins, parities, and branching ratios of",
                " the discrete levels for each nucleus involved were",
                " taken from Nuclear Data Sheets (see REL-REF), and the",
                " first 90 levels of 196Au were included (up to",
                "~0.730 MeV). For the levels with unknown spin and",
                " parity, estimates from neighboring levels were made,",
                " while for levels with more than one spin assignment, a",
                " choice was made in order to include a variety of",
                " spin values."
              ]
            }
          ],
